Have you had someone that you loved so much and thought they would always be by your side?  Then one day you wake up and their gone knowing that you will never get to have them anymore?  Never even get to hear their voice again.  And won't even get to expeirence their touch.  You told this person everything because they were the one you felt comfortable telling, but then their gone and you feel so alone and so scared that you will always feel like this. Afraid you will never find someone that you can tell your most deepest thoughts to anymore.  And the longer you feel this way the sorrow and depression turns into anger and it builds up so much that you just start to cry.  You feel better for a while then you start to think about it and it just builds to anger from sorrow again.  After this happens you are never your self again.  You try to make things look like they are ok and you're over it because no one understands but deep down you really arent over it.   You have friends that you can talk to but they never seem to understand and the ones that do just isnt the same as telling your boyfriend or girlfriend.  And even if you only knew the person a few days or weeks or months, they had such a big impact on your life that it will change you forever and you dont know how to deal with the change after they are gone.  You would have a bad day but you could always look forward to their call.  Then one day when you need that person to talk to, they wont be there........

"I cry because I know I dont have him anymore.  I cry because I think of how pathetic I am. And I cry because I think I'll be crying forever"

1. Whatever you do, don't just show up at her house...she runs around in her underwear just like we do.
2. DON'T CHEAT ON HER. It may seem foolproof, but girls tell each other everything about everything. Trust me, she WILL find out and you will be mud.
(whether you did or not, every girl in the universe will find out, dont give them reason to doubt)
3. Beware of every single male relative and all guy friends. Any of them would kick your ass at the drop of a hat, and a lot of them wouldn't even wait for the damn hat.
4. Never miss an opportunity to tell her she's beautiful.
(make sure she knows you think so, and when she disagrees tell her again)
5. Don't refuse to kiss her in front of your friends. If they laugh at you, it's just because they're jealous.
6. If she slaps you hard, you deserved it.
(dont give her a reason to get that mad at you)
7. Don't be afraid to touch her if you want to. If she's going out with you in the first place, it's because she likes being in your arms.
(hold her close, make her feel secure, dont do it because she asks you to, but because you want to)
8. If you don't sleep with her, DON'T tell your friends that you did.
8.5 If you DO sleep with her, DON'T tell your friends that you did.
9. You can be dirty minded in private, really...most of them are not offended by it...
10. Not all of them eat like birds, a lot of them can eat like whales.
(bring extra cash, and dont make a big deal out of it, or even mention it, it hurts their feelings, and never mention their weight, ever. Even if they are skinny, never tell them they are too skinny, its the same as telling them they are fat, they want to know you love them for who they are, not what you want them to be)
11. Most of them don't mind paying half of everything, but they do discuss these things with their friends. Realize that if you make your girlfriend pay half all the time, everyone will know about it and your friends will know you're a pussy.
11.5 Do you honestly need all your money that much? Be a man, pay all the time!...
(men are supposed to pay all the time, but if you're in a serious relationship its good for her to know that youre alright with her paying, she wont think you want to dominate everything in the realtionship, and what she brings to the table is important to you)
12. Every girl should eventually get three things from her boyfriend- a stuffed animal, one of his sweatshirts, and a really pretty ring. Even if it's not a serious relationship.
13. Make sure she gets home safely as often as you can. If you're dropping her off, walk her to the door. If you aren't dropping her off, call to be sure she's home safely.
14. If a guy is bothering her, it is your right to beat the shit out of him.
15. If you're talking to a female friend of yours, pull your girlfriend closer. 
(and make sure you always introduce them as "your girlfriend")
16. Never, EVER slap her, even if it's just in a joking way. Even if she swats you first, and says, "Oh, you're so dumb" or something, never make any gestures back.
(never hit, or hurt a girl physically, if you do, expect rule ..3 to come into effect, and me to personally beat the shit out of you, or shoot you, whether you know me or not)
17. Go to a chick flick once in a while. She doesn't care whether you enjoy it or not, it just matters that you went.
( dont make a big deal out of it either, let her know if a chick flick is what makes her happy, you're willing to do it, no matter what the event may be, this also applies to her family, she loves her family, and if you love her, you have to learn to love them too)
18. You're dead meat if you can't get along with their pets, parents, and best friends. Be prince charming to their friends, Mr. Polite to their parents, and make sure to be nice to their animals.
19. Don't flirt with their moms...that's just freaky.
( and never comment about their mom being good looking what so ever, if she asks, a good response is, "Yeah she is pretty, but what do you expect of someone who had someone as beautiful as you."
Always defer any talk of beauty to her, her being more beautiful)
20. Don't be freaked out by PMS. It's not gross, and it really does make them feel like shit, so be understanding.
(dont ever ask them if its their time because they are being bitchy, ask them if they need you to do anything for them, again, always give comfort)
21. If you don't like the way they drive, you do it.
( but dont make a big deal out of it, tell them that you prefer to drive and leave it at that)
22. If you're officially dating, and you're introducing her to your friends, you'd better damn well introduce her as your girlfriend.
23. Don't stress where you go for every date. They really only want to be with you.
24. If they complain that something hurts, rub it for them without being asked.
25. Girls are fragile. Even if you're play fighting/wrestling, be very gentle.
26. Memorize their damn birthdays. You forget her birthday and you're basically screwed for life.
( girls think if you really care about them, you shouldn't have a problem remebering things that are important to them, if you dont have a planner, get one even if its for this purpose only, you'll spend less time in the dog house, and more importantly they will know you care)
27. Don't marinade the cologne, but smell good.
(if their ex wore the same cologne, change to something else, girls relate a mans smell to whom it belonged to, always and forever, and you really dont want that complex)
28. Don't give her something stupid for her birthday or Christmas or Valentine's day. It doesn't have to be expensive, but it has to be meaningful. Jewelry is always nice.
(give her something that lets her know you care, car parts, whether needed or not, dont constitute a good gift)
29. If you think the relationship isn't going to last, don't wait to find out. It will only hurt you more if you draw it out.
30. After you've been dating for a while, realize that they really have started to trust you. When you have a girlfriend who truly trusts you, you have a lot more responsibilities, privileges and control than you would think. Be careful with it, most guys would kill for that kind of power, and it can be lost in a nanosecond.
(you dont get a second chance with girls, dont break their trust, and dont put yourself in a position that would allow you to)

You know, I was sitting here thinking.  Im almost a sophemore.  It's great to grow up but honestly, i wish it could be like it used to.  When i was about 4, 5, or 6.  My sister and i had so much fun.  We used to go outside and build club houses and everything.  We had an old metal shed that we would make as our club house.  We'd get cheap little hot wheels and build like humps and play with them in the dirt.  We put some things into an egg and buried it up against the side of the house.  She'd used to take me into the play room and play school with me.  She'd teach me times tables when i was in kindergarden just learning how to write my name. lol  We were good friends with our neighbors and we'd go over and swim with them alot over the summer.  We would go up to my grandma's and play in buckets of water with all of our toys.  In the fall we would rake up a bunch of leaves and play in them.  We loved to go to wyandotte county lake and play in their big play area.  I remember i was afraid to go down the slides. lol  We'd watch Doug, legends of the hidden temple, Wild and crazy kids, and all the other awsome shows that used to be on nickelodeon. One winter we go snowboards from my uncle and we went outside in the winter and would snowboard. I'd always want to do everything my sister did.  I looked up to her alot.  When she got into about 8th grade, she didn't want to do anything with me or hang out with me.  I got really sad cause i wanted it to be like it used to.  I remember we got into a big fight so i made her chocolate milk and took it to her.  I look back at those times that were fun and then i realize they arent coming back.  It just seems like yesterday i was in kindergarden and my sister and i were outside trying to find something to do in the yard. I'm going to be a sophemore soon.  I'm the youngest and in about 3 years it will be my graduation.  It's crazy, its just crazy.  I miss the old days......
